node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Lessons I learned from the book "Rich Dad, Poor Dad." o @er ntrepreneursquote treprer (Ath)'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1) Put your money to work. You cannot get rich with your money in a savings account. You have to invest in appreciating assets.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2) Gain financial knowledge. Learn about investing, business, markets, accounting, sales, etc. It will help you make overall better financial decisions.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3) It isn't about how much you make. How much money you make is important, out what's even more important is how much you KEEP'.
Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4) Acquire assets. Rich people acquires assets while poor accumulates liabilities.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5) You aren't born to to work for others. Most people consider a 9-5 job as something they've supposed to be dealing with for the rest of their lives. Completely forgetting the life possible beyong that.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6) Winning means not being afraid to lose. Never be afraid to take calculated risks. Those who play it safe never make big fortunes.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '7) Pay yourself first. Every month, first invest in your income-generating assets. The rest of expenses should be next to it.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Quick recap: Put your money to work 2. Gain financial knowledge 3. It isn't about how much you make 4. Acquire assets 5. You aren't born to work for others 6. Winning means not being afraid to lose 7. Pay yourself first'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Lessons from the book RICH DAD POOR DAD W THEIR ABOUT MONEY WHAT THE RICH TEACH ROBERTT.KIYOSAKI KIYOSAKI ROBERT Drop a in the comments if you learned something!'.
